<1ST_LINE>r a PM-APAppointment-Ky     05-21 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-AP Appointment-Ky,0117</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>News Editor Appointed in Louisville</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Debra Hale, a newswoman in the Chicago
bureau of The Associated Press, has been named the AP's news editor
in Louisville.
   The appointment was announced Friday by Chief of Bureau Ed
Staats.
   Ms. Hale, 37, joined the AP in Little Rock, Ark., in 1972. She
left in 1975 to teach high school English and returned to the AP in
Little Rock in 1981. She was AP's correspondent in Centralia, Ill.,
in 1983 and the next year transferred to Chicago, where she served
as night supervisor.
   Ms. Hale is from Marked Tree, Ark., and holds bachelor's and
master's degrees from Arkansas State University.
</TEXT>
