<1ST_LINE>r a PM-APAppointment-Iowa     05-21 0114</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-AP Appointment-Iowa,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>News Editor Named in Des Moines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   David Speer, correspondent for The
Associated Press in Iowa City since 1986, has been named the AP's
news editor in Des Moines.
   Chief of Bureau Ruth Gersh announced the appointment Friday.
   Speer, 35, is a native of Little Rock, Ark., where he worked for
the AP for two years before moving to Iowa City. He is a graduate
of the University of Arkansas.
   Speer previously worked for the AP in Jackson, Miss., and for
the Northwest Arkansas Times in Fayetteville. In Des Moines he
succeeds Mark Mittelstadt, who recently was named the AP's chief of
bureau in New Mexico.
</TEXT>
