<2ND_LINE>PM-School Shooting-Chronology,0368</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Day-Long Rampage Leaves Two Dead, Six Injured</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-School Shooting, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINNETKA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology based on reports by
authorities of the events in a rampage by a 30-year-old woman
identified by police as Lori Dann. All times are Central Daylight
Time.
   Friday, 9 a.m. _ The woman plants an incendiary device at
Ravinia School in suburban Highland Park. It is discovered burning
by a worker, but does no damage.
   10:30 a.m. _ A fire starts at a residence where Ms. Dann was
employed as a housekeeper. A mother and two children trapped in the
basement escape through a window, avoiding serious injury. An
unexploded incendiary device is recovered.
   Police said Ms. Dann apparently planted a number of incendiary
devices in North Shore communities.
   10:45 a.m. _ The woman enters the Hubbard Woods Elementary
School and goes into a boys' bathroom, shooting one youngster
there. She then walks into a classroom and tells one teacher a boy
has been wounded. She walks into a second classroom past the
teacher, announces she is carrying a real gun, and opens fire,
striking five children.
   11 a.m. _ The woman leaves the school and heads three blocks
across a wooded area to a home on Kent Road.
   11:30 a.m. _ She chases away four of the home's occupants, but
struggles with a young man, who suffers a gunshot wound in the
chest while wresting away one of several weapons she carries.
   Police arrive with SWAT and hostage negotiating teams, and
maintain a vigil outside the house. They are unable to establish
contact, although they say Ms. Dann spoke with her parents, who
live in the nearby suburb of Glencoe.
   6:40 p.m. _ Police Chief Herbert Timm tells reporters that Ms.
Dann's parents have been brought to the house in an attempt to talk
her out of the residence. He says police are prepared to ``take
action'' if her parents are unsuccessful.
   7:30 p.m. _ Timm reports that a SWAT team searching the house
has found Ms. Dann dead on the second floor. Timm says she shot
herself once in the head with a .32-caliber pistol.
</TEXT>
