``Noriega is not plea bargaining with Reagan and Bush. Reagan and
Bush are plea bargaining with Noriega.''
   
   CRAIG FULLER, the vice president's chief of staff, responding to
the publication of a story in The Washington Post concerning George
Bush's position on negotiations with Noriega: ``The administration
sources who have suggested that the vice president favors ending
the negotiations and bringing the envoy back to Washington are
essentially correct.''
   
   PAUL KIRK, Democratic National Chairman, unleashing a stinging
attack on Bush before the Association of Democratic State Chairs
meeting in Atlanta: ``(he) has neither the toughness to govern nor
the compassion to care.''
