<DOCNO> AP880521-0054 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-05-21-88 0602EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--China-VCRs     05-21 0123</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--China-VCRs,0125</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chinese Can't Get Enough VCRs, Government Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chinese television viewers are snapping up
videocassette recorders far faster than factories can churn them
out, the official daily newspaper said today.
   The Economic Daily said the country will produce 44,000 of the
recorders this year, up from 10,000 produced last year. It said
3,299 VCRs were purchased in Beijing alone in February, a 27
percent increase from the previous month.
   But although 300,000 VCRs are in use nationwide, only one in
every 1,000 Chinese households have the machines, the paper said.
   In contrast, it said, 77 percent of Japanese households have the
recorders. The A.C. Nielsen Co. reported in October that 50.9
percent of the U.S. households have VCRs.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
