<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Crash     05-21 0125</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Crash,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bus Collides With Train, Killing Five</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least five people were killed and 50
injured when a freight train plowed into a passenger bus at a rail
crossing on a main highway, police and hospital officials said
today.
   The bus had apparently stalled on the crossing about 40 miles
southeast of Harare on Friday when the locomotive smashed into it.
   Four men and a woman were killed. All the injured were bus
passengers on their way to Harare for the weekend from villages in
southeastern Zimbabwe, officials said.
   Welders from a nearby factory helped police, firefighters and
other rescue workers free passengers trapped in the bus' mangled
wreckage.
   The locomotive, dented in the front, remained on the tracks.
</TEXT>
