<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BrownArrest     05-21 0478</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Brown Arrest,0496</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>James Brown's Wife Arrested On Drug Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUGUSTA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of soul singer James Brown was
arrested on drug charges one day after her husband was released
from jail on similar charges.
   Adrienne Brown, 38, of Beech Island, S.C., was arrested Friday
upon her arrival at Bush Field airport in Augusta by police acting
on a tip, said Ron Maher of the Augusta police vice and narcotics
unit.
   On Thursday, Brown was released from jail in nearby Aiken
County, S.C., after posting $24,218 bond. He was arrested Wednesday
on charges including possession of drugs; he claimed his wife had
planted the drugs on him.
   Narcotics investigators with a search warrant confiscated a wet,
leafy substance they suspected was the drug PCP, also called
``angel dust,'' from Mrs. Brown as she walked through the airport
parking lot.
   Police said they later found two vials of a substance believed
to be PCP hidden in Mrs. Brown's blouse. She was charged with
possession of the drug.
   Mrs. Brown was released late Friday after posting $10,000 bond.
   Mrs. Brown was arrested April 9 on drug charges in Augusta. She
claimed a friend of her husband had set her up. She also faces a
charge of possession of PCP in Bedford, N.H.
   Brown's arrest Wednesday was his third in six months. Last
November, he was charged with resisting arrest and leaving the
scene of an accident.In April, he was charged with assault with
intent to kill his wife and with assault and battery of a high and
aggravated nature.
   ``It's getting to the point where we're spending a lot of time
investigating Mr. Brown's domestic problems,'' said Capt. James
Whitehurst of the Aiken County Sheriff's Department.
   Brown was charged Wednesday with with possession of PCP,
resisting arrest, illegal possession of a pistol, failure to stop
for a police car and simple assault and battery.
   Brown said he was working ``to keep the city and the world
clean'' from drugs. ``I don't have a drug problem,'' he said.
   Brown said he had not resisted arrest, only tried to ``keep from
being thrown to the ground.''
   He said he was carrying a pistol because he had a large amount
of money and ``important papers.''
   Brown is scheduled to appear June 6 in Aiken County General
Sessions Court. Mrs. Brown has filed for divorce, and Brown said he
plans to do the same.
   Brown, known to his fans as ``The Godfather of Soul,'' may have
to cancel his upcoming European tour because of his most recent
arrest.
   The bond Brown posted Thursday bars him from leaving the state,
Aiken County Magistrate Max Meeks said. Meeks said Brown, who has a
ranch at Beech Island, would need Meek's approval or that of a
circuit judge before leaving.
   Brown was allowed to tour in Brazil while out on bond in April.
</TEXT>
