<HEAD>Indian Air Force MiG Crashes, Pilot Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Indian air force pilot was killed
when his MiG-21 plane exploded Saturday while flying over the
northern state of Kashmir, United News of India reported.
   The pilot was on a training mission when the explosion occurred
over the village of Kakpora, 15 miles north of the state capital of
Srinagar, UNI said.
   The cause of the explosion was not immediately known.
   Of about 600 airplanes belonging to the Indian air force, most
are Soviet-made MiGs.
</TEXT>
