<HEAD>Two Buses Collide, Causing Minor Injuries</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS lead to fix time element, SUBS 4th graf to locate high
school</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two school buses carrying 87 people
collided at a highway toll station, leaving 18 people with minor
injuries, authorities said Saturday.
   Most of the people were treated for neck pains after a bus
carrying students from the Woonsocket Junior High School struck
another bus as they returned from a New York City field trip.
   The first vehicle had stopped for a toll booth on Interstate 95
northbound in New Rochelle when the second rear-ended it Friday
night.
   The injured were taken to New Rochelle Hospital for treatment.
One girl was kept overnight for observation, while the others were
treated and released, said Tim Connors, principal of the school in
Woonsocket, Rhode Island.
   ``All of the other youngsters are fine,'' he said.
   The driver of the bus that was hit was given a ticket for not
having a log and the second driver was ticketed for having
inadequate brakes and not having a log, police said.
