<2ND_LINE>AM-Dukakis-Pressure,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Despite Cool Image, Dukakis' Blood Pressure `At the High End of
Normal'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democratic front-runner Michael Dukakis may
give the appearance of a cool technocrat, but the presidential
candidate's blood pressure is ``at the high end of normal,'' a
doctor said Saturday.
   During a visit to a Los Angelese community health center, Dr.
Pedro Lopez administered a blood pressure test to the Massachusetts
governor. The reading was 138 over 82, which Lopez described as
within the normal range although slightly elevated and ``at the
high end of normal.''
   ``There's steadiness,'' Dukakis said of the reading. ``It may
not be a passionate blood pressure but it's steady.''
   When Lopez gave the same blood pressure test to Kitty Dukakis,
the candidate's wife, the reading was much lower _ 118 over 78.
   ``Amazing,'' Dukakis said of the results for his far more
emotional wife.
</TEXT>
