<1ST_LINE>r a AM-GradeSuicide     05-21 0234</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Grade Suicide,0239</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Blame Suicide of Boy, 10, on Bad Report Card</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 10-year-old boy, apparently despondent over a bad
report card, shot himself to death with a gun taken from his
parents' bedroom, police said.
   Omar Williams shot himself in the chest with a .357 Magnum on
Friday afternoon while his parents were shopping and his brother
and sister were outside playing, said Metro-Dade homicide Detective
Jim McDermott.
   ``It was a shock. I mean someone you have in your own class .. .
and he was so young,'' said Omar's reading teacher, Joan Ziperson.
``He was well-liked. Occasionally, he would do more than his share
of talking.''
   The boy's principal, Betty Meares, said his father came to
school that same day to pick up Omar's report card because he
apparently had failed to take it home. The May report card is only
a progress report for parents and does not determine whether a
student is passed or failed.
   McDermott said the boy's grades were ``were fairly low'' but
were not failing.
   Meares said the only previous fatality since she has been the
school's principal occurred two years ago, when a student was
killed in a traffic accident.
   ``That was terrible, but we've certainly never been through
anything like this,'' she said. The school would probably bring in
counselors to help the other children discuss the suicide, she said.
</TEXT>
