<FILEID>AP-NR-05-21-88 1652EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Sweden-Palme     05-21 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Sweden-Palme,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Slain Swedish Leader Said Extremists Dogged Him</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Olof Palme wrote that
``extremists are hounding me and other Social Democrats'' two days
before he was assassinated on a downtown street, a newspaper said
Saturday.
   The letter, dated Feb. 26, 1986, is believed to be the last that
Palme wrote. It was published in full in the Stockholm newspaper
Aftonbladet.
   Palme was replying to a socialist woman in southern Sweden who
felt persecuted by a small local extreme rightist group.
   He told her, ``Personally, I am not unused to being persecuted
by various extremist groups, and I do not care about it.''
   Palme was shot from behind and killed while walking home with
his wife from a movie in downtown Stockholm.
   Authorities have investigated many leads, including the
possibility of an extremist conspiracy, but no one has been charged
in the slaying.
</TEXT>
