<HEAD>Dutch Prince Drives Into Ditch, Not Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LEIDEN, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dutch Crown Prince Willem Alexander
drove his car into a canal Saturday but escaped uninjured, Dutch
television reported.
   The 21-year-old heir to the Dutch throne, who is a history
student here, apparently lost control over his automobile as he was
approaching a road construction site, according to the television
report.
   The car ran over a grass embankment and into the 12-foot wide
canal, the report said. Willem Alexander climbed out, reached the
shore and reported immediately to a first aid post, the report said.
   It gave no further details of the accident.
   Police said the car was not completely covered by water.
