<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Teacher-Topless     05-21 0273</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Teacher-Topless,0281</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Charged With Having Students Dance Topless</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SARASOTA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sarasota County's teacher of the year has
been charged with having five 17-year-old girls dance topless for
him in a class.
   David John Schram, 34, also faces a count of battery for holding
one of the student's breasts Feb. 9 during class at Booker High
School in Sarasota, police said.
   Schram, who has taught at Booker for 10 years and directs the
school's Visual and Performing Arts Center, refused comment Friday
as he left the Sarasota County Jail after posting $250 bail.
   In an affidavit, police Detective Terry Winkel said that during
dance and drama classes on Feb. 8 and 9, Schram instructed the five
girls ``to take off their tops.'' Schram ``then instructed the
students to dance in place while he walked around viewing their
performance.''
   A boy student also was instructed to remove his clothes above
the waist during the rehearsals. The five girls and a boy were the
only students present, Winkel said.
   Because the girls danced ``with their breasts exposed while he
watched, (Schram) committed the act of sexual performance of a
child,'' according to the warrant issued by Circuit Judge James
Parker.
   The personnel director for the Sarasota County School Board,
Walter Pierce, said detectives contacted school officials after one
of the students and her parents filed a complaint with police in
March.
   Pierce said Schram has been suspended with pay at least until
the June 7 meeting of the Sarasota County School Board.
   Schram was selected from 34 candidates as Sarasota County
Teacher of the Year for the 1987-1988 school year.
</TEXT>
