<HEAD>Democrats Fire Convention Communications Director</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Democratic National Convention Committee
has fired its communications director after complaints from the
news media that preparations for the July 18-21 convention were
inadequate.
   Bob Ferrante was dismissed last week as communications director
for the Democratic National Committee by Don Fowler, the
convention's chief executive officer.
   The firing occurred after a national press tour of convention
facilities on Monday, when the media complained about the state of
arrangements for the 15,000 media representatives who will cover
the convention.
   ``We just agreed it would be better for everybody concerned,''
Fowler said Saturday. ``We needed someone with more technical
knowledge.''
